# Do Not Use
Notes : Google Keep

+fast syncing
+well integrated into Android and Google Ecosystem

-deep-dive into Google Ecosystem which is not wished for privacy
-Closed Source
-Notes are stored unencrypted on Google servers (potential data harvesting)

# Do Use
Notes : Notesnook, CrystalPad, CipherNotes

Option Notesnook : End-to-End Encryption (E2EE) by default. Zero-knowledge architecture, meaning even the developers cannot read your notes. Open Source, clean UI, and acts as a direct, privacy-respecting replacement for Google Keep or Evernote. Cross-device.

Option CrystalPad : A minimalism Note Taking App with OLED option, Open Source. Add Notes easily.

Option CipherNotes : A privacy-first, open-source, E2E-Encryption Notes App. You can add Checklistst and set secret Notes with a Password.
